<p>
   <table><tr><td width=2 bgcolor="#cc0000"></td>
   <td>
   <b><font color="#cc0000">
   Exercise SEQ4.5:</font></b> 
   
   Let A be any event in <b>R</b><sup>n</sup>. Let
   
   <blockquote>
   P(A,&mu;,&sigma;) = P((Z<sub>1</sub>,...,Z<sub>n</sub>) in
   A), 
   </blockquote>
   
   where (Z<sub>1</sub>,...,Z<sub>n</sub> are iid N(&mu;,&sigma;). As
   &sigma; 
           <img src=
           "resources/statinf2/rarrow.png"
           align=middle>
           
            
            <img src=
            "resources/statinf2/inf.png"
            align=top>
            
             show that
   
   <blockquote>
   sup<sub>A</sub> 
   |P(A,&mu;<sub>1</sub>,&sigma;) - P(A;
   &mu;<sub>2</sub>,&sigma;)| 
                              <img src=
                              "resources/statinf2/rarrow.png"
                              align=middle>
                              
                               0.
   </blockquote>
   
   [Hint: In this notation the last exercise has already shown that 
   
   <blockquote>
   
   |P(<b>R</b><sup>n</sup>,&mu;<sub>1</sub>,&sigma;) -
   P(<b>R</b><sup>n</sup>; 
   &mu;<sub>2</sub>,&sigma;)| 
                              <img src=
